newsitem.title: USA: US West Coast distillates rise modestly late.
newsitem.headline: US West Coast distillates rise modestly late.

text.p: U.S. West Coast distillate prices rose modestly late on Thursday as repairs at Unocal's Los Angeles refinery and a flurry of buying ahead of pipeline scheduling lent support.
"There seemed some some scheduling-inspired buying at the end of the day," one dealer said.
Operators shut Unocal's 125,000 barrel per day crude unit early Thursday but expected it back on-line in three days.
Bids for jet fuel in Los Angeles rose 0.50 cent from midday to 71.50 cents a gallon.
CARB diesel bids also rose a half cent to 71.50 cents.
Meanwhile, low sulphur material was unchanged at 68.50/69.50 cents.
Conventional-grade gasoline in Los Angeles remained flat after rising a half cent early, staying 66/67 cents a gallon.
CARB-grade gasoline also flattened, ranging 69.50/70.50 cents.
CARB and conventional grade gasolines in San Francisco were 3.50 cents below Los Angeles material.
